1
00:01:36,110 --> 00:01:40,990
=Yummy Yummy Yummy=

2
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:43,900
=Episode 17=

3
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:49,070
This family

4
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,270
really have a lot of sly ideas.

5
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:53,620
Your Highness,

6
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:55,740
Mr. Lin has already gone
to look for them.

7
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:57,340
What should we plan to do?

8
00:01:57,860 --> 00:01:58,740
Not eating?

9
00:01:59,660 --> 00:02:01,300
Shame on you!

10
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:03,660
Send someone to pursue immediately.

11
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,440
Make sure to bring the Shen family back

12
00:02:05,580 --> 00:02:06,900
before him.

13
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:07,860
Yes.

14
00:02:11,260 --> 00:02:12,420
For the sake of this family,

15
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,460
Lin Yan actually disregarded his dignity

16
00:02:14,460 --> 00:02:15,660
to come to me and ask for them.

17
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:19,580
They are far more influential

18
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,300
than I imagined.

19
00:02:23,540 --> 00:02:25,580
But this family is so cunning.

20
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:27,380
They actually managed to escape.

21
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,590
Otherwise, we would have pried the truth
out of them.

22
00:02:32,780 --> 00:02:34,980
Rather than using the Shen family
to manipulate Lin Yan,

23
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,100
there is actually a simpler method.

24
00:02:38,620 --> 00:02:39,460
Go ahead.

25
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,090
Get rid of him.

26
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:46,100
I know

27
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,660
you've raised him for many years

28
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:48,700
and cannot bear to do it.

29
00:02:50,580 --> 00:02:52,340
But raising a tiger invites disaster.

30
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,370
We'll talk about it later.

31
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:14,660
Run quickly!

32
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:15,620
Run!

33
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:20,730
Yangyang.

34
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:21,700
Yangyang.

35
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:23,100
Are you OK, Yangyang?

36
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:23,940
Get up quickly.

37
00:03:24,660 --> 00:03:25,900
What's wrong with you?

38
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:27,660
Can't you walk carefully?

39
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:29,020
If my baby gets injured,

40
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:30,260
I won't let this go with you.

41
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:31,100
My fault. My fault.

42
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:32,620
Yangyang, did you get injured?

43
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,060
We've been running for a long time.

44
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,520
And this road is hard for both people
and horses to travel.

45
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,060
How about we take a break?

46
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,760
They won't be able to catch up
for a while.

47
00:03:40,770 --> 00:03:41,500
Take a break.

48
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,030
I really can't run anymore.

49
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:45,260
Have a break.
They don't catch up.

50
00:03:45,270 --> 00:03:46,130
Let me check on you.

51
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:47,020
Are you OK?

52
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:49,060
Did you hurt yourself?

53
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,260
I'm sorry, Yangyang, I'm sorry.

54
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:53,180
Be careful, Jicai.

55
00:03:54,780 --> 00:03:56,100
We found the fruit!

56
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:57,620
Auntie, grandma,

57
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:59,420
do you think this grass is edible?

58
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:00,820
Let me go over and take a look.

59
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:01,940
Father.

60
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:03,610
OK.

61
00:04:03,620 --> 00:04:04,860
Let me take a look.

62
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:06,220
Look at this.

63
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,590
- What did you pick, Yangyang?
- Shaojie.

64
00:04:07,590 --> 00:04:08,700
Get up and work.

65
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:10,220
Why are you always lying here?

66
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:11,780
What's it?

67
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,460
Jicai, look.

68
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,780
Yangyang, where did you pick this?

69
00:04:17,780 --> 00:04:18,940
Right in here.

70
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,060
Look, there's plenty of them.

71
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:24,540
This... this seems to be smartweed.

72
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:25,780
Is it spicy?

73
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:27,340
What is it? Is it edible?

74
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:28,620
We have to taste it.

75
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:29,460
If it is smartweed,

76
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:30,460
then it is edible.

77
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:32,180
But then, who will taste it?

78
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:34,780
Do we have to learn from Shennong
and taste all kinds of herbs?

79
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:36,550
Yangyang, you even know
how to use allusions.

80
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:37,820
Better than your father.

81
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:40,890
You found something to eat?

82
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:42,460
What's this?

83
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:46,020
Father, why did you eat it?

84
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,500
- Gongcai...
- Father!

85
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:51,090
Father!

86
00:04:51,220 --> 00:04:52,060
- Father!
- Gongcai!

87
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:52,900
Gongcai, come on.

88
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:54,950
Spit it out! Hurry up.

89
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:56,500
- Hurry up.
- Spit it out.

90
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,940
Spit it out.

91
00:04:58,060 --> 00:04:58,980
- Come on.
- Father,

92
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:00,360
- Spit it out.
- Spit, spit, spit.

93
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,860
- Father...
- Spit it out.

94
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:03,060
Spit, spit.

95
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:03,900
Alright, alright.

96
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:05,380
Alright.

97
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:06,780
Did you spit it out?

98
00:05:06,780 --> 00:05:09,700
Father, you're choking me to death.

99
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,180
- Feel better?
- It's fine.

100
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:13,220
This thing

101
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,460
is so spicy.

102
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:16,140
- It's spicy?
- It's spicy.

103
00:05:17,460 --> 00:05:19,340
It means that it is edible.

104
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,540
Then we can cook spicy dishes.

105
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:21,660
Hot and sour noodles.

106
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:23,940
Boiled fish in spicy soup.

107
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,460
Mapo tofu.

108
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,460
Spicy chicken cubes.

109
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:28,020
Spicy boiled blood curd.

110
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:33,940
Auntie,

111
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:35,740
can we bring back more smartweed?

112
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:36,900
I want to eat spicy strips.

113
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:39,540
Yangyang, you want to eat,

114
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:40,940
why not let me make it for you?

115
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:43,020
You definitely don't know
how to make it.

116
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:44,660
Don't worry.

117
00:05:44,660 --> 00:05:46,980
I just dug up several plants
of smartweed.

118
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:49,360
Maybe I can even set up
a special section for spicy dishes.

119
00:05:49,690 --> 00:05:51,740
Spicy chicken, spicy fried duck,
Mapo tofu.

120
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:54,040
Much more useful than the dogwood
they like to use here.

121
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:56,510
That's why we still have
to be in the human world;

122
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,560
hell won't do,

123
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,950
we can't even get spicy food there.

124
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:01,060
The last one.
You all aren't eating it, huh?

125
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:02,160
If you don't, I'll take it.

126
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,300
Father, I want it too.

127
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,100
Yangyang,

128
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,660
let's play rock-paper-scissors.

129
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:07,650
Whoever wins gets to eat.

130
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:08,660
I'll count to three.

131
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:09,900
I'll play paper, OK?

132
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,220
Come on, one,

133
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,190
two,

134
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:13,100
three.

135
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,140
I win!

136
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,280
- Shen Shaojie, you cheat?
- Shen Gongcai.

137
00:06:17,290 --> 00:06:18,140
You naughty boy!

138
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:19,180
Just for something to eat,

139
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,580
you even lied to your own daughter.

140
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,180
Mother, how come you don't know
how to joke either?

141
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:24,300
I'm just teasing her.

142
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,000
She can't even trust her own father.

143
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,100
When she grows up, she won't

144
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,620
be deceived by another man, right?

145
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,460
Well,

146
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:30,740
you're always in the right.

147
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,440
Yangyang, don't be angry.
I'm kidding.

148
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,380
Let me take it for you.

149
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:39,300
Grandma.

150
00:06:39,460 --> 00:06:40,300
Don't move.

151
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:41,460
Don't... don't move.

152
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:43,300
You're hiding here.

153
00:06:43,580 --> 00:06:44,700
We finally found you.

154
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:45,750
Did they put

155
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:46,710
a tracking system on us?

156
00:06:46,710 --> 00:06:47,660
They actually found us.

157
00:06:47,660 --> 00:06:49,300
Stop that. Take Yangyang away quickly.

158
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:50,780
Yes, Jicai,

159
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:51,860
you go with Yangyang.

160
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:53,980
I want to let them know

161
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,700
what it means to be a heroine.

162
00:06:56,210 --> 00:06:57,900
Mother, can you handle this?

163
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:58,980
You don't understand her.

164
00:06:58,980 --> 00:06:59,990
She is absolutely capable.

165
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:01,160
When I was young,

166
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,290
I trained in discus throwing.

167
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:04,020
Hear that? This is why it hurts so much

168
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,260
every time she pinches me.

169
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:07,660
You've got quite some guts,
even started chatting.

170
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,100
Jicai, hurry up and go.

171
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,140
Hurry, take Yangyang away.

172
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:10,860
Let's go!

173
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:11,860
Catch them!

174
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:40,460
Yangyang.

175
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,100
I really can't run anymore.

176
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,580
Go, quickly.

177
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:54,600
Auntie.

178
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:55,480
Here.

179
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,340
Come. Quick.

180
00:07:56,420 --> 00:07:57,540
Here, hide inside.

181
00:07:57,540 --> 00:07:58,980
OK. Auntie, you come in too.

182
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:00,980
Auntie.

183
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,180
You can't get away.

184
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,140
Yangyang, just hide here.

185
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:10,980
Don't make a sound.

186
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,950
I'll make spicy strips for you
after I come back.

187
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:14,720
Don't make a sound.

188
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:15,990
Auntie...

189
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,220
You little brat, come here.

190
00:08:20,220 --> 00:08:21,220
Come catch me.

191
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,780
Weren't you acting tough just now?

192
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:35,420
Discus throwing or something.

193
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:36,270
Let me...

194
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:37,580
What are you doing?

195
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:39,750
Father!

196
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:40,660
Fengxia.

197
00:08:45,180 --> 00:08:46,020
Jianshe...

198
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:48,380
You're courting death.

199
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:01,700
You're the ones courting death.

200
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:02,880
- Mr. Lin.
- Are you alright?

201
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:04,820
Take this message back.

202
00:09:05,050 --> 00:09:06,780
If you lay a hand
on the Shen family again,

203
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:08,980
I will never let it slide.

204
00:09:09,660 --> 00:09:10,500
Let's go.

205
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,740
Get lost.

206
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,140
Just wait and see.

207
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,460
- Mr. Lin.
- Where are Jicai and Yangyang?

208
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:16,900
They ran in that direction.

209
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:18,500
Let's go.

210
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:19,640
- Go.
- Go.

211
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:20,780
Take care.

212
00:09:22,090 --> 00:09:22,960
Yangyang.

213
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,280
- Lady Shen.
- Be careful!

214
00:09:24,620 --> 00:09:25,580
- Jicai.
- Yangyang.

215
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:26,740
Be careful, be careful.

216
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:27,780
Yangyang.

217
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,100
- Yangyang.
- Lady Shen.

218
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:31,820
Jicai.

219
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:33,210
Yangyang.

220
00:09:33,470 --> 00:09:34,310
Yangyang.

221
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,540
- Jicai.
- Shen Shaoguang.

222
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:36,530
Yangyang.

223
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:38,180
Be careful.

224
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:39,960
Yangyang.

225
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:41,140
Yangyang.

226
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:42,980
Answer me.

227
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:43,980
Jicai.

228
00:09:44,180 --> 00:09:45,300
- Mr. Lin.
- Shen Shao...

229
00:09:46,260 --> 00:09:48,140
Mr. Lin, I'm here.

230
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:49,460
Yangyang.

231
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:50,430
- Over there.
- Hurry.

232
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:52,420
- Coming.
- I'm here.

233
00:09:52,420 --> 00:09:54,660
- Yangyang.
- Mr. Lin, I'm here.

234
00:09:54,940 --> 00:09:55,980
I'm here.

235
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,180
- Father.
- Yangyang.

236
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,780
- Grandpa, grandma.
- Yangyang.

237
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,620
Yangyang, are you OK?

238
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:02,990
- Did you hurt?
- Are you injured?

239
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:04,580
Are you OK?

240
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:06,860
- Yangyang.
- Where is your auntie?

241
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:07,700
Where is Jicai?

242
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:09,580
Yangyang, was auntie running with you?

243
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:11,380
My auntie diverted the bad guys

244
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:13,580
to save me.

245
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:17,140
She hasn't come back.

246
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:19,100
Yangyang, which way did your auntie go?

247
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:20,500
That direction.

248
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:54,060
Stop going further.

249
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:56,420
Come back with me obediently.

250
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:58,540
I promise not to take your life.

251
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:02,620
Mr. Lin.

252
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:12,340
If it weren't useful to keep you alive,

253
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,840
you wouldn't have the chance
to play tricks with me here.

254
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:17,180
Since you're so good at causing trouble,

255
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:19,170
I'll cut off your hands and feet

256
00:11:19,180 --> 00:11:20,470
and mutilate you.

257
00:11:20,540 --> 00:11:21,420
No, no, no.

258
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:22,540
If so, it's meaningless

259
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:23,600
to take me as the hostage.

260
00:11:23,660 --> 00:11:25,620
It's better to have four limbs intact.

261
00:11:25,780 --> 00:11:27,340
I will never lie to you again.

262
00:11:31,580 --> 00:11:32,420
Mr. Lin.

263
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:35,260
Do you think I will believe you
a second time?

264
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:51,900
She told you the truth,

265
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,140
but you don't believe it.

266
00:11:54,890 --> 00:11:55,740
Mr. Lin.

267
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,590
Are you OK?

268
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:58,020
It's dangerous here.

269
00:11:58,020 --> 00:11:58,860
Let's go first.

270
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:07,580
Shaoguang.

271
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:18,260
Hold on to me.

272
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:21,100
Mr. Lin, save me. Save me.

273
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:21,940
Don't worry.

274
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:23,900
I will definitely get you up.

275
00:12:24,580 --> 00:12:26,860
Mr. Lin, do not let go.

276
00:12:26,860 --> 00:12:28,100
I haven't lived enough yet.

277
00:12:28,460 --> 00:12:30,380
There are still many things
I haven't eaten yet.

278
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,980
I haven't yet made the Shen's Diner

279
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:32,900
bigger and stronger.

280
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,220
I also said I want

281
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:36,500
to make affordable food for everyone.

282
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,020
I swear on my life,

